President Obama commends the decision made by President Thein Sein of Burma to release hundreds of political prisoners, describing it as a significant step towards democratic reform. He highlights the discussions he had with Aung San Suu Kyi and President Thein Sein on how America's engagement can help empower democratic reform and improve relations between the two countries. The President also mentions the positive developments that have occurred since Secretary of State Hillary Clinton's visit to Burma, including the announcement of elections and a ceasefire agreement with the Karen National Union. President Obama urges the Burmese government to ensure that all former political prisoners are allowed to fully participate in the political process and calls for the release of all remaining prisoners of conscience. He expresses his commitment to continuing engagement with the government and taking additional steps to build confidence and support democratic governance and national reconciliation in Burma.